// test/Lower/m3_corpus/s28/pass.test — M5 T106 / FR-030 / SC-003.
// Auto-generated golden-diff harness paired with pass.expected.mlir.
// Asserts `nslc -emit=mlir` on the M3 Sema pass-case fixture for
// constraint s28 produces byte-identical output to the captured
// golden. Regression-guard: any visitor change that silently mutates
// lowering output for an M3 fixture flips this test red.
//
// XFAIL CLOSED 2026-05-04 by M4 amendment #8 — `nsl.state` parent
// trait widened from `HasParent<"ProcOp">` to
// `ParentOneOf<["ModuleOp", "ProcOp"]>`, mirroring the NSL grammar
// shape (top-level `state s { }` defs as siblings of `proc p`).
// `FirstStateOp::verify` and `GotoOp::verify` updated to also resolve
// state-name targets at module scope when the proc body lacks them.
//
// RUN: %nslc -emit=mlir %S/../../../sema/s28/pass.nsl > %t.actual.mlir
// RUN: diff %t.actual.mlir %S/pass.expected.mlir
